{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 review (G6 — approach soundness). Findings posted to the structured review channel; summary: the chosen approach (server-side writes via B-DM's existing `/prompt/save` seam, dropdowns from the enumerate API, overlay `when` sourced from the workflow's own `overlay_triggers` outputs) is sound and codebase-aligned — no superior structural alternative. One coaching item: the plan treats \"criterion\" and \"prompt\" authoring as two symmetric things, but in this codebase a batch criterion references a `prompt:` id (e.g. `criteria: [{prompt: tests}]` in batch-demo.yaml). Clarify whether \"author a new criterion\" is just prompt-authoring (reusing `save_prompt`/index-regen) or a distinct library, since the create mechanism + drift-gate path differ."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782502362442263001,"uuid":"e18859e3-e0e4-495e-815e-d65d9a4f5c4e"}